> Pork chops are always a dinner winner. They're satisfying, speedy, and so
> versatile, which is why our chefs are always thinking up new ways to take
> them to the next level. This week's version comes together in just 30
> minutes, with minimal cleanup required thanks to our handy oven-ready
> aluminum trays. We glaze spice-rubbed pork chops with tangy-sweet BBQ sauce,
> then roast right alongside ready-to-bake biscuits and lemony green beans.
> We call that the perfect busy weeknight meal.

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Wash and dry all produce. Place @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings)
in a #small bowl{}; set aside to soften.

Pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g} and @salt{}. Place in 1
@oven-ready aluminum tray{3} (divide between 2 trays for 4 servings). Brush
tops of pork with half the @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving).

Roast on top rack until cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @green beans{6%ounce} in another aluminum tray (divide
between 2 other trays for 4 servings); toss with a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%teaspoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add to top rack (middle rack for 4); roast for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove from oven, carefully stir, then return to oven until tender,
~{5-8%minutes} more.

When green beans have roasted 5 minutes, remove @buttermilk biscuits{6%ounce}
from package. Place in an even layer in remaining aluminum tray (remaining
trays for 4 servings).

Bake on middle rack until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

To bowl with softened butter, add @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4
servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}; stir to combine. (Use remaining garlic powder
as you like.)

> TIP: If butter is not yet softened, microwave for a few seconds.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Drain excess liquid from green beans if necessary; toss
with a squeeze of lemon juice.

Divide pork, green beans, and biscuits between plates. Top pork with
remaining BBQ sauce. Brush biscuits with some garlic butter. Serve with
remaining garlic butter on the side.